def _cython_agg_blocks(
    self, how: str, alt=None, numeric_only: bool = True, min_count: int = -1
) -> "Tuple[List[Block], Index]":
    data: BlockManager = self._get_data_to_aggregate()
    
    if numeric_only:
        data = data.get_numeric_data(copy=False)
    
    agg_blocks: List[Block] = []
    new_items: List[np.ndarray] = []
    deleted_items: List[np.ndarray] = []
    
    group = self.groupby(self.grouper)
    result = group.aggregate(how=how, axis=0, min_count=min_count)
    
    for name, agg_value in result.iterrows():
        # Convert the aggregated value to the original dtype
        agg_value = maybe_downcast_to_dtype(agg_value, orig_dtype=data.dtypes[name])
        # Create a Block with the aggregated values
        agg_block: Block = make_block(agg_value, items=[name])
        agg_blocks.append(agg_block)
        new_items.append(data.get_pos_dict()[name])
    
    # Rest of the code to handle split blocks and return agg_blocks and agg_items
    
    return agg_blocks, agg_items
